<div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:.62rem;letter-spacing:.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mid)">Pillar One</div>
<div style="font-family:var(--display);font-size:1.05rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--ink);line-height:1.2">The Service Model Approach</div>
</div>
</div>
<p style="font-size:.88rem;color:var(--mid);line-height:1.72;margin-bottom:10px">Authority in a federated institution is not granted by title – it is <em>earned by delivering value first</em>. UD&amp;AS positioned itself as a resource that schools wanted to use, not a mandate they were required to follow. By investing in each school's individual fundraising success before asking for data reciprocity, UD&amp;AS built the trust necessary to introduce shared infrastructure.</p>
<div style="background:#fff;border-left:3px solid var(--cr);padding:10px 14px;font-size:.82rem;color:var(--cr2);font-style:italic;border-radius:0 3px 3px 0">"We lead with what we can give, not what we need. When schools see UD&amp;AS as their best resource, coordination follows naturally."</div>
<div style="margin-top:12px;display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:6px">
<span class="badge badge-cr">Value-first approach</span>
<span class="badge badge-lt">School autonomy preserved</span>
<span class="badge badge-gd">Central data as a service</span>
