</div>
</div>
<p style="font-size:.88rem;color:var(--mid);line-height:1.72;margin-bottom:10px">When two schools identify the same major gift prospect, conflict is inevitable without a principled resolution process. The <strong>Collaborative Outreach and Facilitated Decision (COFD)</strong> framework replaces competition with a structured arbitration protocol: the school with the strongest relationship owns the primary cultivation role; the second school receives stewardship credit and a co-cultivation seat at the table. Decisions are documented, transparent, and final.</p>
<div style="background:#fff;border-left:3px solid var(--gold);padding:10px 14px;font-size:.82rem;color:#5A3A00;font-style:italic;border-radius:0 3px 3px 0">"A donor approached by a unified Harvard – not three competing offices – is more likely to make a transformational gift. COFD turns institutional rivalry into institutional strength."</div>
<div style="margin-top:12px;display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:6px">
<span class="badge badge-gd">Prospect arbitration protocol</span>
<span class="badge badge-lt">Shared credit model</span>
<span class="badge badge-cr">Conflict → coordination</span>
</div>
</div>
