<div style="width:34px;height:34px;background:var(--ok);border-radius:50%;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;color:#fff;font-size:.85rem;font-weight:700;flex-shrink:0">3</div>
<div>
<div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:.62rem;letter-spacing:.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mid)">Pillar Three</div>
<div style="font-family:var(--display);font-size:1.05rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--ink);line-height:1.2">Transparency as Trust</div>
</div>
</div>
<p style="font-size:.88rem;color:var(--mid);line-height:1.72;margin-bottom:10px">The Central Donor Master succeeds only if every school trusts that the data will be used to help them – not to monitor, constrain, or override their strategy. Radical transparency means schools can see exactly what data is shared, with whom, under what conditions, and to what end. The Dean's Consensus Tracker is not a surveillance tool; it is a shared instrument that every school can read and that protects their prospects as much as it coordinates them.</p>
<div style="background:#fff;border-left:3px solid var(--ok);padding:10px 14px;font-size:.82rem;color:#1A4026;font-style:italic;border-radius:0 3px 3px 0">"Schools that can see everything they contribute to the shared layer – and everything they receive – are schools that keep contributing. Opacity kills federated systems."</div>
<div style="margin-top:12px;display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:6px">
<span class="badge badge-gn">Full data visibility</span>
<span class="badge badge-lt">Bilateral accountability</span>
<span class="badge badge-blue">Dean's Consensus Tracker</span>
</div>
