<h2>1. Automated Propensity Scoring (Python · XGBoost)</h2>
<h4>What This Does – Plain English</h4>
<p>Harvard has 400K+ alumni. It's impossible to manually evaluate who might be ready to give a major gift. This script runs <strong>every night at 3am</strong> and produces a score (0–1) for each alumnus – like a credit score, but for philanthropic readiness. Monday morning, every gift officer gets a ranked list: <em>"These 50 people are most ready to hear from you this week."</em></p>
<div class="sflow">
<div class="sbox"><div class="snum">Input</div><div class="stitle">Alumni Data</div><div class="sdesc">Giving history, events attended, wealth signals, email opens</div></div>
<div class="sbox"><div class="snum">Model</div><div class="stitle">XGBoost AI</div><div class="sdesc">Trained on 10yrs of Harvard giving outcomes · 84% precision</div></div>
<div class="sbox"><div class="snum">Output</div><div class="stitle">Priority List</div><div class="sdesc">Top 50 "ready now" prospects per gift officer</div></div>
<div class="sbox"><div class="snum">Action</div><div class="stitle">Gift Officer</div><div class="sdesc">Uses list to book calls, visits, President trip stops</div></div>
</div>
<div class="chart-wrap sm" onclick="expandChart('autoAccChart','Propensity Model Accuracy FY22–FY26')" style="margin-bottom:16px"><div class="chart-label">Model Precision &amp; Prospects Surfaced – FY2022 to FY2026</div><div class="chart-hint">click to expand ↗</div><canvas id="autoAccChart"></canvas></div>
<h4>The Code</h4>
<pre><span class="c"># udas_propensity.py – nightly batch scoring (SYNTHETIC DEMO)</span>
<span class="k">import</span> pandas <span class="k">as</span> pd
<span class="k">import</span> xgboost <span class="k">as</span> xgb
<span class="k">from</span> sqlalchemy <span class="k">import</span> create_engine
<span class="k">from</span> sklearn.preprocessing <span class="k">import</span> StandardScaler
<span class="k">import</span> mlflow

ENG = create_engine(os.environ[<span class="s">"UDAS_WAREHOUSE"</span>])

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="n">load_features</span>():
    <span class="k">return</span> pd.read_sql(<span class="s">"""
        SELECT c.constituent_id,
               wp.estimated_capacity,    – DonorSearch + iWave ensemble
               wp.wealth_score,          – 1–10 normalized
               g.lifetime_giving,
               g.years_since_first_gift,
               g.gift_count_5yr,
               e.events_attended_3yr,
               e.email_open_rate,
               e.reunion_participation_flag,
               a.school_count,           – multi-school affiliation flag
               a.is_board_member,
               liq.liquidity_events_6mo  – IPO / M&amp;A / vesting signal
        FROM constituent c
        LEFT JOIN wealth_profile wp    ON wp.constituent_id = c.constituent_id
        LEFT JOIN giving_summary g     ON g.constituent_id  = c.constituent_id
        LEFT JOIN engagement_summary e ON e.constituent_id  = c.constituent_id
        LEFT JOIN affiliation_rollup a ON a.constituent_id  = c.constituent_id
        LEFT JOIN liquidity_events liq ON liq.constituent_id = c.constituent_id
        WHERE c.deceased = false AND c.opt_out_modeling = false
    """</span>, ENG)

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="n">score</span>(df):
    <span class="k">with</span> mlflow.start_run(run_name=<span class="s">"udas-propensity-v3"</span>):
        model = xgb.XGBClassifier()
        model.load_model(<span class="s">"models/propensity_v3.json"</span>)
        X = StandardScaler().fit_transform(df.fillna(<span class="v">0</span>).drop(columns=[<span class="s">"constituent_id"</span>]))
        df[<span class="s">"p_5yr_gift"</span>]   = model.predict_proba(X)[:,<span class="v">1</span>]
        df[<span class="s">"p_principal"</span>]  = df[<span class="s">"p_5yr_gift"</span>] ** <span class="v">2.4</span>  <span class="c"># tail-weighted for $5M+ asks</span>
        df[<span class="s">"model_version"</span>] = <span class="s">"v3.1.2"</span>
        mlflow.log_metric(<span class="s">"rows_scored"</span>, len(df))
        mlflow.log_metric(<span class="s">"high_propensity_count"</span>, (df[<span class="s">"p_principal"</span>] &gt; <span class="v">0.75</span>).sum())
    <span class="k">return</span> df[[<span class="s">"constituent_id"</span>, <span class="s">"p_5yr_gift"</span>, <span class="s">"p_principal"</span>, <span class="s">"model_version"</span>]]

<span class="k">if</span> __name__ == <span class="s">"__main__"</span>:
    out = score(load_features())
    out.to_sql(<span class="s">"propensity_score"</span>, ENG, if_exists=<span class="s">"replace"</span>, index=<span class="k">False</span>)
    print(<span class="s">f"✅ Scored {len(out):,} constituents. High-propensity: {(out.p_principal &gt; 0.75).sum()}"</span>)</pre>
</div>
<div class="card cr-acc">
<h2>2. Wealth Screening Refresh – Ensemble Model</h2>
<h4>What This Does – Plain English</h4>
<p>We buy wealth data from three vendors (DonorSearch, iWave, WealthEngine). Sometimes they disagree wildly on a donor's estimated net worth. This script <strong>reconciles the three signals</strong> into a single trusted number, and flags any case where vendors disagree by more than 30% for a human researcher to review.</p>
<pre><span class="c"># wealth_ensemble.py – SYNTHETIC DEMO</span>
<span class="k">def</span> <span class="n">blend_capacity</span>(ds: float, iw: float, we: float) -&gt; dict:
    <span class="s">"""
    Median-of-three with disagreement alarm.
    If vendors disagree &gt; 30%, flag for manual review queue.
    """</span>
    vals = sorted([v <span class="k">for</span> v <span class="k">in</span> [ds, iw, we] <span class="k">if</span> v <span class="k">is not None</span>])
    <span class="k">if not</span> vals:
        <span class="k">return</span> {<span class="s">"capacity"</span>: <span class="k">None</span>, <span class="s">"flag"</span>: <span class="s">"NO_DATA"</span>}
    median = vals[len(vals) // <span class="v">2</span>]
    spread = (max(vals) - min(vals)) / median <span class="k">if</span> median <span class="k">else</span> <span class="v">0</span>
    flag = <span class="s">"REVIEW_REQUIRED"</span> <span class="k">if</span> spread &gt; <span class="v">0.30</span> <span class="k">else</span> <span class="s">"ACCEPTED"</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> {
        <span class="s">"capacity"</span>: round(median, <span class="v">-4</span>),  <span class="c"># round to nearest $10K</span>
        <span class="s">"flag"</span>: flag,
        <span class="s">"spread_pct"</span>: round(spread * <span class="v">100</span>, <span class="v">1</span>),
        <span class="s">"sources"</span>: {<span class="s">"donor_search"</span>: ds, <span class="s">"iwave"</span>: iw, <span class="s">"wealth_engine"</span>: we}
    }

<span class="c"># Example: $10M (DS), $8M (iWave), $12M (WE) → median $10M, 40% spread → REVIEW</span>
result = blend_capacity(<span class="v">10_000_000</span>, <span class="v">8_000_000</span>, <span class="v">12_000_000</span>)
<span class="c"># → {"capacity": 10000000, "flag": "REVIEW_REQUIRED", "spread_pct": 40.0}</span></pre>
</div>
<div class="card cr-acc">
<h2>3. Gift Administration Velocity – SQL Dashboard</h2>
<h4>What This Does – Plain English</h4>
<p>When a donor sends a $5M check, it must be received, verified, coded, processed, acknowledged, and audited. Our target is <strong>under 48 hours</strong> for all gifts. This SQL view powers the live VP dashboard and fires an alert automatically if any gift exceeds the SLA window.</p>
<div class="sflow">
<div class="sbox"><div class="snum">Receive</div><div class="stitle">Gift Arrives</div><div class="sdesc">Check, wire, stock, or bequest notification</div></div>
<div class="sbox"><div class="snum">Code</div><div class="stitle">Auto-Classify</div><div class="sdesc">AI suggests fund code + school allocation</div></div>
<div class="sbox"><div class="snum">Process</div><div class="stitle">Human Review</div><div class="sdesc">Gift officer confirms within SLA window</div></div>
<div class="sbox"><div class="snum">Acknowledge</div><div class="stitle">Auto Thank-You</div><div class="sdesc">Personalized letter generated same-day</div></div>
<div class="sbox"><div class="snum">Audit</div><div class="stitle">GAAP Record</div><div class="sdesc">Compliance trail auto-logged</div></div>
</div>
<pre><span class="c">-- velocity_view.sql – powers VP Husson live dashboard (SYNTHETIC DEMO)</span>
<span class="k">CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW</span> v_gift_admin_velocity <span class="k">AS</span>
<span class="k">SELECT</span>
  date_trunc(<span class="s">'month'</span>, accepted_at)                              <span class="k">AS</span> month,
  school_code,
  count(*)                                                       <span class="k">AS</span> gifts_processed,
  round(avg(extract(<span class="n">epoch from</span> finalized_at - accepted_at)
    / <span class="v">86400.0</span>), <span class="v">1</span>)                                              <span class="k">AS</span> avg_days,
  percentile_cont(<span class="v">0.95</span>) within group
    (<span class="k">ORDER BY</span> finalized_at - accepted_at)                        <span class="k">AS</span> p95_days,
  sum(<span class="k">CASE WHEN</span> amount &gt;= <span class="v">1000000</span>  <span class="k">THEN</span> <span class="v">1</span> <span class="k">ELSE</span> <span class="v">0</span> <span class="k">END</span>)           <span class="k">AS</span> seven_fig_count,
  sum(<span class="k">CASE WHEN</span> amount &gt;= <span class="v">10000000</span> <span class="k">THEN</span> <span class="v">1</span> <span class="k">ELSE</span> <span class="v">0</span> <span class="k">END</span>)           <span class="k">AS</span> eight_fig_count,
  <span class="c">-- SLA breach: &gt; 48hrs for standard, &gt; 4hrs for 8-figure gifts</span>
  sum(<span class="k">CASE WHEN</span>
    (amount &lt; <span class="v">10000000</span> <span class="k">AND</span> finalized_at - accepted_at &gt; interval <span class="s">'48 hours'</span>) <span class="k">OR</span>
    (amount &gt;= <span class="v">10000000</span> <span class="k">AND</span> finalized_at - accepted_at &gt; interval <span class="s">'4 hours'</span>)
  <span class="k">THEN</span> <span class="v">1</span> <span class="k">ELSE</span> <span class="v">0</span> <span class="k">END</span>)                                           <span class="k">AS</span> sla_breaches
<span class="k">FROM</span> gift_lifecycle
<span class="k">WHERE</span> finalized_at <span class="k">IS NOT NULL</span>
<span class="k">GROUP BY</span> <span class="v">1</span>, <span class="v">2</span>
<span class="k">ORDER BY</span> <span class="v">1</span> <span class="k">DESC</span>, avg_days <span class="k">DESC</span>;</pre>
</div>
<div class="card cr-acc">
<h2>4. Federated Master ID Matcher (Cross-School Deduplication)</h2>
<h4>What This Does – Plain English</h4>
<p>Twelve schools each have their own donor records. The same person might appear as "John R. Smith" in one system and "J. Robert Smith" in another. This script links all records for the same person across all 12 CRMs – ensuring no donor is ever double-counted or double-solicited.</p>
<pre><span class="c"># master_id_matcher.py – Fellegi-Sunter probabilistic match (SYNTHETIC DEMO)</span>
<span class="k">from</span> recordlinkage <span class="k">import</span> Index, Compare, ECMClassifier

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="n">link_school_to_master</span>(school_df, master_df):
    <span class="s">"""
    Probabilistic record linkage across 12 School CRMs.
    Uses Jaro-Winkler name similarity + birth year + email domain.
    Generates the lookup_id that anchors every Central Donor Master record.
    """</span>
    indexer = Index()
    indexer.block(<span class="s">"last_name"</span>)  <span class="c"># block on surname for performance</span>
    candidate_pairs = indexer.index(school_df, master_df)

    cmp = Compare()
    cmp.string(<span class="s">"first_name"</span>, <span class="s">"first_name"</span>,  method=<span class="s">"jarowinkler"</span>, threshold=<span class="v">0.85</span>)
    cmp.exact( <span class="s">"birth_year"</span>, <span class="s">"birth_year"</span>)
    cmp.string(<span class="s">"email_domain"</span>, <span class="s">"email_domain"</span>, method=<span class="s">"levenshtein"</span>, threshold=<span class="v">0.70</span>)
    cmp.geo(   <span class="s">"lat"</span>, <span class="s">"lng"</span>, <span class="s">"lat"</span>, <span class="s">"lng"</span>, method=<span class="s">"exp"</span>, offset=<span class="v">1.0</span>)

    features = cmp.compute(candidate_pairs, school_df, master_df)
    matches  = ECMClassifier().fit_predict(features)
    <span class="k">return</span> matches  <span class="c"># multi-index of matched (school_id, master_id) pairs</span></pre>
