  adoptionChart:`<h4>Executive Reading</h4><p>Data literacy is now an operating risk, not a training footnote. Schools below proficiency need targeted enablement before campaign launch so prospect strategy is comparable across units.</p><ul><li>Best-practice benchmark: 85-90% active adoption before major campaign launch.</li><li>Mock-data note: school maturity levels are illustrative.</li></ul>`,
  themeHeatmap:`<h4>Executive Reading</h4><p>This chart is a decision map, not a decoration. It shows where donor interest, school readiness, timing, and gift capacity create a clear next action.</p><ul><li><strong>Highest action score:</strong> send to President/dean briefing.</li><li><strong>Medium score:</strong> keep with school gift officer until case language is ready.</li><li><strong>Low score:</strong> useful for stewardship or future cultivation, but not immediate leadership time.</li></ul>`,
  themeOpportunityChart:`<h4>Executive Reading</h4><p>This companion chart converts donor interest into a practical ask portfolio. It helps leadership see which themes have enough ready pipeline to justify briefing time.</p><ul><li>AI and financial aid are the strongest near-term asks.</li><li>Sustainability needs a blended case: campus operations plus research.</li><li>Civil discourse should remain quiet-phase until language is aligned.</li></ul>`,
  matrixConsensus:`<h4>Executive Reading</h4><p>The matrix shows where school autonomy is working with central intelligence and where data-sharing norms are still fragile. Low consensus areas should receive governance support before the feasibility study.</p>`,
